*   **Re-evaluate the Spectral Index Derivation:** The current derivation of $n_s$ appears to rely on an effective field theory approach that may be inconsistent with the graviton condensate framework. Re-derive $n_s$ using the *fluctuation-dissipation theorem* applied specifically to the Bogoliubov mode density, rather than standard slow-roll parameters. If the model cannot produce $n_s \approx 0.96$ without extreme tuning, acknowledge this as a potential tension rather than a success.
