**3. Forward-Looking Insight:**
The most valuable next step is to determine if the model predicts a specific relationship between the tensor-to-scalar ratio $r$ and the number of species $N_s$. If the model forces $r$ into a specific range (e.g., $r > 10^{-3}$), it becomes testable by upcoming experiments. Focus the next iteration on deriving this $r(N_s)$ relation analytically to provide a concrete target for CMB-S4.

